Reports surfaced Monday that Tennessee sophomore offensive tackle Brett Kendrick had been ruled out for the season with an injury, but multiple program sources refuted those claims to GoVols247. 
Two program sources said Monday afternoon that Kendrick — Tennessee's first-team right tackle — was indeed continuing to battle with elbow and knee problems, but that Vols coach Butch Jones ’ comments from earlier in the day were accurate.
